########On Kali, confirm network interface & IP:

ifconfig                                                # (from PDF) — or `ip a` (recommended modern)


#####33On target Windows XP / Metasploitable check IP (inside target VM):

ipconfig                                                # (from PDF)
# or on Linux target: ifconfig


########3Quick discovery (on Kali) to find live hosts:

netdiscover -r 192.168.1.0/24                            # (recommended) adjust subnet
# OR
netdiscover                                              # (from PDF reference)


#####33Nmap host & port scan (verbatim normalized from PDF):

nmap -T4 -sS <target-ip>                                 # (from PDF, normalized)
# example: nmap -T4 -sS 192.168.1.105


##########Save scan output to file (explicit save example — useful):

nmap -T4 -sS -oN metasploitable.nmap <target-ip>         # (recommended)
cat metasploitable.nmap                                  # view saved results (from PDF)


##Use Legion (GUI) — open from Start menu in Kali:

####3GUI step: Menu → Legion → enter root password → specify IP subnet and bits → submit. (PDF shows GUI; no single command). 


############DNS enumeration (examples from PDF):

nslookup <domain>                                       # find IP, mail servers etc. (from PDF)
dig <domain> MX                                         # recommended for mail servers (from PDF)
dig <domain> NS                                         # recommended for name serve
